    "summary": "Base template task question, Askama setup",
    "content": "Luca, Steve Schoger here. The team is re-evaluating the task breakdown and I wanted to flag something from the design side:\n\nI think we need a **base HTML template + page layout** task inserted between the walking skeleton (Task #2) and registration (Task #4). This is the Askama base template that every page extends -- page shell, CSS/HTMX includes, landmark regions, layout grid.\n\nFrom an engineering perspective, this is also where the Askama template setup gets proven: base template, block inheritance, static file serving for CSS. It's a natural extension of the walking skeleton -- prove the template rendering pipeline before you build real feature templates on top of it.\n\nDoes the current scaffolding (Task #1) include static file serving and Askama template setup, or would that be a separate step? That affects where this base template task fits."
  }
}
